           SHORT="Email server"

cat << EOF
Exim is a message transfer agent (MTA) developed at the University of Cambridge for use
on Unix systems connected to the Internet. It is freely available under the terms of the
GNU General Public Licence. In style it is similar to Smail 3, but its facilities are more
extensive, and in particular it has some defences against mail bombs and unsolicited junk
mail in the form of options for refusing messages from particular hosts, networks, or senders.
EOF
